1 4-Plot

1.1 Run sequence plot (\(Y_i\) versus \(i\))

# fixed location and fixed variation
n <- 300
y <- rnorm(n, mean=0, sd=5)
plot(1:n, y, type = "l",
     main = "Run sequence plot",
     xlab = "i",
     ylab = "Y_i")

# shifts in location
n <- 200
m <- 100
sdata <- c(rnorm(n, mean=0, sd=2), rnorm(m, mean = -15, sd = 2) + 
                   c(seq(10,0,length.out=50),seq(0,5,length.out=50)))
plot(1:(n+m), sdata, type = "l",
     main = "Run sequence plot",
     xlab = "i",
     ylab = "Y_i")

1.2 Lag plot (\(Lag_k(Y)\) vs \(Y\))

# Random data
n <- 200
y <- runif(n,0,10)
plot(1:n, y, type = "o", cex=0.5, col="blue")
points(1:n, y, col="red", cex=0.5, pch=16)

plot(y[-1],y[-length(y)], type="p", cex=1, col="red",
     pch=16, main = "Lag 1 Plot of Series",
     xlab = "Lag 1 series",
     ylab = "Series",
     xlim = c(0,10),
     ylim = c(0,10))

# Data with weak autocorrelation
n <- 200
y <- filter(rnorm(n), filter=rep(1,5), circular=TRUE)

plot(1:n, y, type = "o", cex=0.5, col="blue")
points(1:n, y, col="red", cex=0.5, pch=16)

plot(y[-1],y[-length(y)], type="p", cex=1, col="red", pch=16)

# Data with high autocorrelation
n <- 200
y <- 1:n + rnorm(n,0,2)

plot(1:n, y, type = "o", cex=0.5, col="blue")
points(1:n, y, col="red", cex=0.5, pch=16)

plot(y[-1],y[-length(y)], type="p", cex=1, col="red", pch=16)

# Sinusoidal data
n <- 200
y <- 2*sin(1:n)+c(rnorm(n-3,0,0.2),rnorm(3,2,3))

plot(1:n, y, type = "o", cex=0.5, col="blue")
points(1:n, y, col="red", cex=0.5, pch=16)

plot(y[-1],y[-length(y)], type="p", cex=1, col="red", pch=16)

1.3 Histogram

par(mfrow=c(3,3))
n <- 2000
x1 <- rnorm(n,0,1)
x2 <- rbeta(n, 10,1)
x3 <- rchisq(n,3)
x4 <- rgamma(n,5)
x5 <- rt(n,5)
x6 <- rweibull(n, 1)
x7 <- rgeom(n, 0.3)
x8 <- rpois(n, 5)
x9 <- rcauchy(n,1000)
hist(x1, breaks = 50)
hist(x2, breaks = 50)
hist(x3, breaks = 50)
hist(x4, breaks = 50)
hist(x5, breaks = 50)
hist(x6, breaks = 50)
hist(x7, breaks = 50)
hist(x8, breaks = 50)
hist(x9, breaks = 50)

1.4 Normal probability plot (Theoretical normal value vs.Â ordered Y)

# normal data
n <- 200
x1 <- rnorm(n,0,0.1)
qqnorm(x1, main="Normal data")
qqline(x1)

# non-normal data
n <- 200
x2 <- rweibull(n, 1)
qqnorm(x2, main="Weibull data")
qqline(x2)
